            <div class = "hero">
                <h2>The Research Equity Lens</h2>
            </div>
            <p>Our platform improves the scientific rigor of studies by providing targeted follow-up criteria for specific conditions like Endometriosis. This section ensures that researchers look beyond surface-level data to capture a more complete biological picture:</p>
            <ul>
                <li style = "color: #6935B3"><strong>Captures Overlooked Biological Markers:</strong> Prompts researchers to include data on cyclical systemic symptoms (bowel, bladder, and referred pain) often ignored in traditional "male-centric" study designs.</li>
                <li style = "color: #6935B3"><strong>Refines Patient Stratification:</strong> Helps researchers categorize participants not just by gender, but by specific symptom clusters and life-impact metrics to ensure more accurate subgroup analysis.</li>
                <li style = "color: #6935B3"><strong>Standardizes Inclusive Methodology:</strong> Provides a framework for researchers to report race, family history, and long-term diagnostic delays, ensuring the research reflects the true diversity of the patient population.</li>
            </ul>
